The following is required to apply for a Mining Permit in South Africa as stipulated by the Department of Mineral Resources: Provide a plan as contemplated in Regulation 2(2) read with Regulation 2(3) of the Mineral and Petroleum Resources Development Act (MPRDA). Provide detailed documents proving that the applicant has the technical ability and financial resources that are readily available or how they will be provided for. This will enable the applicant  to carry out the mining activities and to mitigate as well as rehabilitate environmental impacts. Provide details of any mineral or minerals and the quantity thereof, which the applicant intends to remove and dispose of during mining operations. An amount of R100 application fee is payable as specified in regulation 75(1) (d) of the MPRDA. An individual applicant must attach a certified copy of the identity document. A certified copy of the certificate issued by the Companies and Intellectual Property Commission (CIPC). All applicants are required to apply for the necessary environmental authorisation in terms of the National Environmental Management Act (NEMA), 2008 and the National Environmental Waste Management Act (NEWMA), 2008 in respect of listed activities that have been triggered by applications in terms of the MPRDA, 2002 as amended. NOTE: NEMA PRICING R2 000  c/o Meintjies and Francis Baard Streets Sunnyside Pretora  enquiries@dmr.gov.za samradonline@dmr.gov.za www.dmr.gov.za   78 De Korte Street c/o De Korte and De Beer Braamfontein Johannesburg  Save Ways Crescent Centre c/o OR Tambo and Mandela Road Witbank  9459 The Strip building 314 Stateway and Bok Streets Welkom  Old Premier House 101 Dorp Street Polokwane  Durban Bay House 333 Anton Lembede Street Durban  Pier 14 Shopping Centre 444 Govan Mbeki Avenue Port Elizabeth  PRD Building 96 Sutherland Road Mthatha  Ascension House c/o Riebeeck and Lower Burg Streets Cape Town  Perm Building 65 Phakamile Street c/o Mabitja Street Kimberley  Hopley Centr